"The whole point of bringing up the eye example is to demonstrate that ID is an actual theory, and not a simple example in which someone proclaims that something is too complex based on their own judgements."- richardsonkrIf ID is an "actual theory," no doubt the answers to the following questions should be simple to produce.1. What mechanisms are described by the Theory of Intelligent Design?2. What predictions are made by the Theory of Intelligent Design?3. How is the Theory of Intelligent Design falsifiable?4. What observations are considered evidence for the Theory of Intelligent Design?